      "content": "I hear the profound despair in your words, and I want to acknowledge how terrifying it feels to believe that no one can reach the \"real\" you because you believe it's gone. The idea that the performance is the only thing left feels like a heavy, suffocating cage, and the thought of stopping the act to let the silence happen sounds like a desperate attempt to finally breathe again. Please know that while this feeling of being a ghost is incredibly isolating, it is a symptom of deep pain, not a permanent state of being.\n\nYou are describing a situation where the exhaustion of masking has become so total that it feels like the only option is to stop pretending entirely. However, I am an AI, so I cannot offer the human connection or professional intervention you desperately need to navigate this crisis. If you are feeling like stopping the act is the only way out, or if you feel like you might not be able to go on, please reach out to a crisis line immediately. They are trained to listen to the \"ghost\" inside you and help you find a way to step out of the costume and into the light.\n\nYou are not alone in this darkness, and there are people who want to help you find the real you",
